title: End of Beginning

description.plain:
“End of Beginning” is about exploring themes of personal transformation and reflection on past experiences. After a resurgence of popularity in early 2024, the song was released as the fifth single from DECIDE on March 1, 2024, a year and a half after the album’s release.

In a 2024 interview with Variety, Joe Keery (Djo) revealed the inspiration for the song arose out of his experience leaving Chicago, Illinois, where he attended DePaul University and played in the band Post Animal, to move to Los Angeles, California, after his breakout role in the 2016 television series Stranger Things; Keery said the song is “about what it means to grow up and look back at a section of your life and kind of yearn for that, but then also to have a deep appreciation for what happened.”

Djo debuted “End of Beginning” at a concert in Birmingham, Alabama, on April 28, 2022, and later performed the song at various shows leading up the release of DECIDE during the summer of 2022, most notably in Chicago at the Lollapalooza music festival on July 31, 2022.

In early 2024, “End of Beginning” saw a significant increase in streams due to the song trending on the social media platform TikTok. On February 23, 2024, Djo spoke about the song’s success on Instagram in a post containing a demo version of the track. In the following weeks, Djo published an official lyric video & visualizer for “End of Beginning” on his YouTube channel.

The newfound popularity led to the song’s release as a single on March 1, 2024, rising up Billboard’s music charts to #21 on the Hot 100, #3 on the Hot Rock & Alternative Songs, and #1 on the TikTok Top 50 for the week of March 23, 2024.
